      "name": "Hemolysis index validation at 3.5 L/min, 2400 RPM",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at the nominal operating point (3.5 L/min, 2400 RPM). Predicted NIH = 0.0023 g/100 L; measured NIH = 0.0025 ± 0.0004 g/100 L. Agreement within 8%, satisfying the ±15% acceptance criterion. The Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law model with linear damage accumulation reproduces experimental data at this single condition.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "8% relative error in NIH at nominal operating point",
      "passFail": "Pass"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/mesh-convergence-gci",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Grid convergence index study — centrifugal pump hemolysis mesh",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (0.8 M, 3.1 M, 11.4 M cells) performed at the nominal operating point. GCI for NIH between medium and fine meshes is 2.3%, below the 5% threshold. Medium mesh (3.1 M cells) selected for production runs.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "GCI = 2.3% (NIH, medium-to-fine)",
      "passFail": "Pass"
