      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted NIH within ±15% of measured NIH at the validation operating point.",
      "rationale": "CFD NIH = 0.0023 g/100 L versus measured 0.0025 g/100 L; relative error 8%. Criterion of ±15% satisfied. Note: validation performed at a single operating point (3.5 L/min, 2400 RPM); the linearity assumption underpinning the power-law damage accumulation model is implicitly satisfied at this condition but is not independently tested across the full five-point COU operating envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (NIH and relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint; QoI sensitivity to operating condition variations demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "NIH and RH are established surrogates for clinical hemolysis in pump V&V literature (ASTM F1841). Sensitivity analysis across 5 operating points demonstrates RH varies from 0.61 to 0.94, confirming discriminatory power. Criterion met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid properties, and operating conditions sufficiently similar to COU device and operating envelope to support extrapolation.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry identical to COU device. Fluid properties matched. Validation at 3.5 L/min and 2400 RPM is within the COU operating envelope (2–6 L/min, 1800–3000 RPM). The Giersiepen–Wurzinger model requires that damage accumulation be linear and path-independent; this precondition is satisfied at the validation point but the package does not include evidence verifying linearity at the four remaining COU operating points, particularly the high-flow (6 L/min) and low-speed (1800 RPM) extremes where shear-rate trajectories differ substantially."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 beyond code verification already assessed.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error beyond discretization and code verification is scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Accepted as not-assessed."
    },
