      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualification documented separately.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment not required at MRL 2. Analyst holds CFD certification; peer review of setup documented in project record. Accepted as not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selection justified with supporting literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on rotating machinery literature review (Menter 1994; Bludszuweit 1995). Hemolysis model: Giersiepen–Wurzinger power law (C=3.62e-7, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785). Model form justified by published comparisons against FDA pump benchmark. The model is theoretically valid under the assumption that cumulative damage is a linear functional of the stress-exposure scalar — an assumption that holds in the quasi-steady laminar-dominant regime observed at the nominal validation point but which has not been verified for the transient high-shear trajectories expected at 6 L/min, 3000 RPM. This theoretical precondition is stated in the source literature but no verification activity is included in this package to confirm it holds across the full COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
