    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cv-lab-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors accepted as not-assessed per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 at MRL 2. Validation at the nominal operating point (3.5 L/min, 2400 RPM) demonstrates NIH prediction within 8% of measured values. The Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis model is accepted as fit-for-purpose based on demonstrated agreement at the validated condition and supporting literature. The assessment team notes that the linearity-of-damage-accumulation precondition cited in the model form rationale is satisfied at the validated operating point; the team accepts this as sufficient evidence for MRL 2 without requiring explicit verification across all five COU operating points. Decision: Accepted for submission.",
